comments: White (BOS) is drawn into the air by the pump fake and swipes down, initiating illegal contact with Love (MIA) that affects his shot attempt near the rim. Horford (BOS) makes clean contact with the ball as he contests and head/face contact occurs during the follow-through.   Contact to an opponent's head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
Tatum (BOS) extends his arm outward as he releases from the contact with Herro (MIA), but the contact is marginal.
Adebayo (MIA) is in the paint for less than three seconds when the shot is imminent.
Lowry (MIA) stops and establishes himself in Brown's (BOS) path and marginal contact occurs to Brown's side as he contests the shot during the pick.
Love (MIA) grasps and then immediately releases Horford's (BOS) jersey as the two engage.
Horford (BOS) places and removes his hand from Adebayo's (MIA) back and the contact during his upward shooting motion is marginal.
Lowry (MIA) uses his left arm to hold down Holiday's (BOS) right arm and the contact affects his ability to pursue the rebound.
Brown (BOS) extends his arm outward and marginal contact occurs with Butler's (MIA) arm as Butler attempts to pass.

Replay review of the foul called on Butler (MIA) pursuant to a coach's challenge was deemed unsuccessful. Butler (MIA) reaches in and initiates contact with White's (BOS) arm during the drive that causes him to lose control of the ball.
Adebayo (MIA) establishes screening position and firms up over his left foot in Tatum's (BOS) path and does not deliver illegal contact as the screen is set.
Butler (MIA) hands the ball off and establishes position in front of Tatum (BOS) without extending into his path or delivering contact.
White (BOS) and Adebayo (MIA) get tangled as they mutually engage during the rebound.

Brown (BOS) brings his left arm off the ball after securing the rebound and contact occurs with Lowry's (MIA) head.  Contact to an opponent's head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
